<br />

<br />
You can't nuke the whole fight due to aggro control anyway. You can't dish out damage any faster than you can cast.  Our wizards are being fed mana from necros using the group mana spell, and they rarely run out anyway.
<br />

<br />
Benefit to the clercis?  Sure, of course.  They get another CH in the rotation.  The people casting remove curse can cast 6 more times or so.... Course it's cheap enough it doesn't matter anyway. 
<br />

<br />
1600 HP or so to the entire raid?  Nice, might lose one less person to Curses or AEs, but the main mob is probably hitting for 800-1200 a pop, so it's not helping the MT....
<br />

<br />
Basically, it isn't that overwhelming as you might think.  Manaburn was nerfed because it was too much damage at one time from one person.  Ours would be less powerful than druids mgb'ing their hp /ac/ds equivalent... Though still nice.
