<span class="postbody">First of all the mgb hp aspect of paragon is moot. Druids have spirit of wood and clerics have EE which do as much or more.
<br />

<br />
Then the ONLY issue is the mana component. To be honest I can't think of any fights where this would be critical except one or two (emporer being one of them). Most fights in PoP require strategy rather than endurance. I have been in very few raids that failed from lack of mana as opposed to MT going down and the rest falling like skittles; or an add getting into casters and killing enchanters.
<br />

<br />
It gets to the point where an mgb would be convenient but no more. It would not make or break a raid any more than a regular paragon. Rather than thinking in total terms of mana over the period, remember that it is 80 mana a tick for up to 48 seconds. On high end raids most people are on 50+ a tick anyhow. Really it only amounts to between half and 3/4 of a bubble for the our casters. 
<br />

<br />
Shere Khaan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
